option.WAVING_COBWEB=Waving Cobweb
option.WAVING_COBWEB.comment=Waving Cobweb

option.LOWPOLY_WATER=Low-poly Water
option.LOWPOLY_WATER.comment=Uses only vertex offsets for waves on water. Looks cool, not realistic. Currently broken!

option.CINEMATIC_MODE=Cinematic Mode
option.CINEMATIC_MODE.comment=Classic letterboxing. Used to simulate a widescreen image being displayed on a taller screen. Good for videos. Bad for screenshots and gameplay.

option.CLAY=Clay Mode
option.CLAY.comment=Everything is made out of clay :D

option.VIGNETTE=Vignette
option.VIGNETTE.comment=Darkens corners of screen.

option.WAVING_CAMERA=Waving Camera
option.WAVING_CAMERA.comment=Waving Camera

option.WAVING_HAND=Waving Hand
option.WAVING_HAND.comment=Waving Hand

option.DOF=Depth of Field
option.DOF.comment=Simulates the way the eye focuses by blurring objects not in focus (DoF). Medium performance impact.

option.centerDepthHalflife=DoF Focus Transition Speed
option.centerDepthHalflife.comment=Adjust how long it takes to change focus. Higher values means longer transition time.

option.APERTURE=Aperture
option.APERTURE.comment=Use bigger values for shallower depth of field.

option.TILT_SHIFT=Tilt Shift
option.TILT_SHIFT.comment=Simulates a Tilt Shift lens. Also known as the "Model Train" effect.

option.DOF_FALLOFF_STRENGTH=Depth of Field Strength
option.DOF_FALLOFF_STRENGTH.comment=Similar to aperture. Higher values means stronger DoF.

option.BLOOM=Bloom
option.BLOOM.comment=Makes objects appear to glow when bright enough. Medium performance impact.

option.BLOOM_STRENGTH=Bloom Strength
option.BLOOM_STRENGTH.comment=Controls the strength of the bloom effect.